<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Bird-of-Paradise - National Emblem of Papua New Guinea</title>

<style>
body {
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    background-color: #f4f4f4;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 20px;
}

.container {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: auto;
    background: white;
    padding: 20px;
    border-radius: 10px;
    box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);
}

h1 {
    color: #b22222;
    text-align: center;
}

img {
    display: block;
    margin: 20px auto;
    width: 300px;
    border-radius: 10px;
}

p {
    font-size: 18px;
    line-height: 1.6;
}

ul {
    font-size: 18px;
}
</style>
</head>

<body>

<div class="container">
    <h1>Bird-of-Paradise</h1>

    <img src="bird-of-paradise.jpg" alt="Bird-of-Paradise">

    <p>
        The Bird-of-Paradise is the national emblem of Papua New Guinea.
        It represents freedom, beauty, unity, and the rich cultural heritage
        of the country.
    </p>

    <h2>Features</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Scientific Name: <i>Paradisaea raggiana</i></li>
        <li>Habitat: Tropical rainforests of Papua New Guinea</li>
        <li>Diet: Fruits, berries, and insects</li>
        <li>Known for its colorful feathers and courtship dance</li>
    </ul>
</div>

</body>
</html>
